Item.Description: A 2016 Grand Final re-match kicks off the final round of the regular season. Swifts v Firebirds for bragging rights

Item.Description: The Vixens can return to top spot with a win against Adelaide, but the Thunderbirds need a big win to avoid the wooden spoon.

Item.Description: Collingwood can lock up a final spot with a win against the Fever in Perth, but West Coast will be keen to ruin the return of old teammates

Item.Description: Sunshine Coast Lightning host the NSW Swifts, with the Queenslanders eyeing off top spot on the Suncorp Super Netball ladder

Item.Description: The Giants could secure a top 2 finish with a win against the Firebirds, but it's also the Queenslanders' last chance.

Item.Description: After giving up a 5 goal lead in the 4th quarter last week, the Fever will be angry. But the Lightning could move up to first place with a big win at home.

Item.Description: The Giants could move up the ladder with a big win in Perth, although the Fever will be out for revenge after going down 66-51 in their first meeting.

Item.Description: Neither side has tasted victory since February and both want to avoid the first ever wooden spoon of Suncorp Super Netball. Adelaide v NSW

Item.Description: Round 10 kicks off with a top of the table battle in Melbourne, as the Lightning try to secure a finals spot against the Vixens.

Item.Description: Last time these two sides met, they couldn't be separated and after some heartbreaking losses of late, the Swifts will be out to break the Vixens unbeaten streak.

Item.Title: 2017 Rd 9: Firebirds v Fever (Replay)
Item.Description: The Fever and Firebirds face off in the second of the Brisbane double header, where the Queenslanders could break into the top 4 temporarily.

Item.Description: Both sides recorded disappointing losses last week, but will be hopeful of turning it around in Round 6. Thunderbirds v Firebirds.

Item.Description: A top of the table clash as Giants Netball head down to Melbourne in hope of continuing their winning streak over the Vixens.

Item.Title: 2017 Rd 5: Lightning v Magpies (Replay)

Item.Title: 2017 Rd 5: Firebirds v Vixens (Replay)
Item.Description: The battle for the finals is heating up, with only percentage separating The Firebirds and Vixens ahead of their clash in the first of a double header in Brisbane.

Item.Title: 2017 Rd 4: Magpies v Thunderbirds (Replay)
Item.Description: Both the Magpies and Thunderbirds lost at home last week and will be looking to get that winning feeling back in round 4 of Suncorp Super Netball.

Item.Description: Top of the table clash in the Sunshine Coast, as Giants Netball travel to the University of the Sunshine Coast in a battle of the undefeated.

Item.Description: It's the rematch of one of sport's greatest Grand Finals ever played. Firebirds v Swifts for the first time in Suncorp Super Netball, to continue a long standing rivalry.

Item.Description: Can the Lightning keep their undefeated start to Suncorp Super Netball running? Adelaide will look to storm past the Sunshine Coast at home.

Item.Description: The West Coast Fever host their first match of Suncorp Super Netball, as the Firebirds travel across the Nullarbor.

Item.Description: The Queensland Firebirds look to get their first win on the board for Suncorp Super Netball when Kim Ravaillion and Magpies Netball come to town.

Item.Description: Giants Netball try to keep their great start to Suncorp Super Netball rolling in the clash against West Coast Fever
